The seat changes reflect the shifts from the [1997 general election](/1997_United_Kingdom_general_election) results. It's worth noting that two seats had already changed hands in by-elections between the general elections:
*   [Romsey](/Romsey_(UK_Parliament_constituency)) transitioned from [Conservative](/Conservative_Party_(UK)) to [Liberal Democrats](/Liberal_Democrats_(UK)). The Liberal Democrats successfully defended this seat in 2001.
*   [South Antrim](/South_Antrim_(UK_Parliament_constituency)) moved from the [Ulster Unionists](/Ulster_Unionists) to the [Democratic Unionists](/Democratic_Unionist_Party). The Ulster Unionists managed to reclaim this seat in 2001.

[Seats won in the election (outer ring) against number of votes (inner ring)](/File:2001_UK_general_election_results_by_seat.svg)

The results of this election yielded a [Gallagher index of disproportionality](/Gallagher_Index) of 17.74, a figure primarily driven by the discrepancies between Labour and the Liberal Democrats.

