### Voter demographics

According to a post-election survey conducted by [MORI](/Ipsos_MORI) interviewing 18,657 adults in Great Britain, the demographic breakdown of the vote was as follows:

[The 2001 UK general election vote in Great Britain (in per cent)](/File:2001_UK_general_election_vote_in_Great_Britain.svg)

The disproportionality of the house of parliament in the 2001 election was 18.03 according to the [Gallagher Index](/Gallagher_Index), primarily reflecting the electoral system's impact on the distribution of seats between Labour and the Liberal Democrats.

